[5] Canada Recall
Date: Thu 2 Apr 2009
Source: Canadian Press [edited]
<http://www.google.com/hostednews/canadianpress/article/ALeqM5jR2GF4XoGwY6ud66VYLfVlUzXyFQ>


The Canadian Food Inspection Agency and Loblaw Brands Ltd. are
warning the public not to consume certain President's Choice brand
Premium Nut Collections and White Chocolate Cranberry Pistachio Bark.
The nationally distributed products contain pistachios recently
recalled in the USA by Setton Pistachio of Terra Bella, Inc., due to
salmonella contamination.

A day earlier, it was announced Frito Lay Canada was voluntarily
pulling Munchies brand pistachios from the marketplace. In either
case, no associated illnesses have been reported.

