******
[6] Philippines Recall
Date: Wed 1 Apr 2009
Source: Manila Bulletin [edited]
<http://mb.com.ph/articles/201090/pistachios-recalled>


The Bureau of Food and Drugs (BFAD) on Wed 1 Apr 2009 ordered a
recall on pistachio products sourced from manufacturer Setton
Pistachio in California following an earlier recall by the US Food
and Drug Administration (FDA) due to salmonella contamination. "We
are recalling all pistachio brands imported from the USA," said BFAD
director Leticia Barbara Gutierrez.

She said inspectors have already collected samples of the products
and are now testing them. Gutierrez said she asked the importers to
pull out their pistachio products via a product recall order. She
said they intended to serve the recall order on Wed 1 Apr 2009,
although importers have already been informed of the BFAD action by
phone. There are 4 licensed pistachio importers in the country who
are sourcing their products from the USA.

[Byline: Jenny F. Manongo, Angie Chui]

